            <p class="core">The rain and mist are the only constants in these landscapes, shifting in an endless cycle. At first, the Ardennes seem untouched by warmth—yet, beneath the quiet, there's a sense of belonging. You feel it in the people, in the simple joys of life, in the unspoken connection of shared moments. No matter where you're from, this place feels like home.
            <br><br>
